## Conversation
User directed: duplicate the TraceServerInterface protocol (and BaseModelStrict)
so they live on both sides; chose EXPLICIT imports over a star-facade; placement
client=weave/trace_server_interface.py, server=weave/trace_server/trace_server_interface.py;
"move all protocols". This is PR1 of the shared->0 contract split.

## What
Four protocols: TraceServerInterface (3050), ObjectInterface (3234),
FullTraceServerInterface (3313) in shared/trace_server_interface.py, and
ServiceInterface in shared/service_interface.py. Removed from shared (by marker,
not line numbers); copied verbatim into a client facade + a server facade.
No `from __future__ import annotations` in the source -> signatures evaluate at
class-def time -> the copies need every referenced type in scope. Derived the
EXACT set via ruff F821 on the protocols-without-model-imports (194 tsi models +
4 service models + the agent_types module alias), imported explicitly. The two
facades are identical except the docstring. Repointed ~28 importers (client->
weave.trace_server_interface, server/tests->weave.trace_server.trace_server_interface);
models stay imported from weave.shared. Added weave.trace_server_interface to all
4 import-linter contracts.

## Errors & Mistakes (brutal honesty)
1. The data-driven repoint script inserted the facade import after the LAST
   `from weave...` line -- which, when that line was a multi-line block OPENER
   (`from weave.shared.errors import (`), put the import INSIDE the block ->
   SyntaxError in 6 server files (evaluation_status, feedback, clickhouse,
   llm_judge, + 2 tests). `import weave` still passed (these are server-only, not
   loaded by the client import) which masked it; lint-imports caught it. Fixed
   with a regex that swaps the misplaced single-line facade import BEFORE the
   block opener.
2. Removing the protocols from shared/tsi made `agent_types` unused there, so
   ruff --fix deleted `from weave.shared.agents import types as agent_types`.
   But external_to_internal_trace_server_adapter.py + test_trace_server_interface_util.py
   accessed it via the INCIDENTAL re-export `tsi.agent_types.X` -> AttributeError.
   Fixed by importing agent_types directly in those 2 files and dropping the
   `tsi.` prefix.

